Package: clifR
Type: Package
Title: Common Longitudinal ICU data Format Tools for R
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: c(
    person("CLIF Consortium", role = "aut"),
    person("Aartik", "Sarma", email = "aartiksarma@example.com", role = c("cre", "aut"))
    )
Description: An R port of the Python library clifpy for standardizing and
    analyzing critical care (ICU) data using the Common Longitudinal ICU data
    Format (CLIF) version 2.0. Provides tools for data validation, unit conversion,
    clinical score calculation (SOFA, Charlson Comorbidity Index), wide dataset
    transformation, and encounter stitching. Designed for high-performance
    processing of large ICU datasets with built-in schema validation.
License: Apache License (>= 2.0)
URL: https://github.com/AartikSarma/clifR
BugReports: https://github.com/AartikSarma/clifR/issues
